extendedInfo.description: NOTE: This application is powered by Fiserv, Inc., but is activated through specific financial institutions. You will have received a text message from your bank or credit union directing you to this site to download the TouchBanking mobile banking application AFTER you register your device within your bank or credit unionâs online banking.Now you can manage your money anytime, anywhere â from your mobile device. With TouchBanking you can conveniently and securely: - Check your account balances - View recent transactions - Transfer money between your accounts - Pay bills - Find ATMs and branch locations In order to enable certain features, this application needs to access the following on your mobile device:- Location services: So we can return ATM/Branch search results that are relevant to your current location- Camera: So that you can use the Mobile Check Deposit feature- Contacts: So that when using the Popmoney person-to-person payments feature you can easily select a contact from your device to paySome of these features may not be enabled for you right now, but may be added by your financial institution in the future.Note that some devices may report that this application requires access to call logs. This is an issue with certain Android versions which incorrectly report this as part of the âContactsâ permission. This application does not and will not access any of your call logs.Fiserv powers online banking and bill pay for thousands of institutions and millions of consumers nationwide. You may not recognize the Fiserv name, but if you use online banking and bill pay, chances are you already use a service that comes from Fiserv.

reviews.title: Suckkssssss
reviews.comment: Constantly says error then when you call back to reset it they have no clue what you\'re talking about. TD Bank app works way better, but I have two bank accounts.

reviews.title: At least it is an app now
reviews.comment: Droid razr maxx HD - I like the old look on the website alot more with everything in 1 view  :-\\
reviews.author: John Lawson

reviews.title: Needs upgrades
reviews.comment: The app works well as far as showing balance but it definitely has bugs. I never can transfer funds from one account to the other.
reviews.author: J\'Marcus Brooks

reviews.title: Problems after upgrade
reviews.comment: App crashes on transfer of funds between checking and savings. Basically only good for balance checking so that means it\'s useless. Please fix the bugs.
reviews.author: David Moquin

reviews.title: Finally
reviews.comment: I\'ve maitained a bank account at Chase only because of the mobile deposits. Now that my dinky-bank offers this app (with mobile deposits) I\'m finally able to close that terriable account. And to those complaining about invasion of privacy - the camera access is for mobile deposit - not to spy on you...

reviews.title: Doesn\'t work
reviews.comment: App says only to go to the store for an update; but, no update is available.  Worked fine before.

reviews.title: Meh
reviews.comment: It\'s ok.  I have it installed on the Samsung Galaxy S4, but there is no option to use decimal values with Mobile Deposit Capture, Transfers or Payments.  Not a huge deal but it is a pain for customers who are with the times.  This is semi-typical of Fiserv products though.  Just a little behind everyone else.

reviews.title: Sucks still
reviews.comment: I have been trying to access this for over a month and it keep giving me an error about the wrong pass word have restalled over 6 times excuse my Frenchnut, FUC DIS SHT Ill just do without
reviews.author: Marilyn GERMANY

reviews.title: Next time, remember the decimal point
reviews.comment: Galaxy S4 unable to use this app. When you enter digits in the deposit section, there is no decimal point on the apps keyboard. What a shame; now I\'ll have to look at using BOA. I\'d rather have all my teeth pulled out.
reviews.author: Frank Arnzen

reviews.title: Looks nice
reviews.comment: I can\'t seem to get it to let me enter my password I click on the section that say password and I get the click noise and no response.

reviews.title: Needs new UI
reviews.comment: This apps UI is based off of 1.6 and the current android UI is 4.0+.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Obvious stupidity
reviews.comment: Ok obviously you guys at fiserv don\'t know what \"user friendly\" is. This app has a very good concept but if American national was able to run on a different app I sure would be using this one. When I go to type my password my keyboard covers up what I\'m typing, even when I\'m transferring money, I can\'t see what I\'ve typed. Also the way to switch from account to account to transfer money from is a joke. This app needs to be fasterand smoother. And USER FRIENDLY!!!
reviews.author: Sam Campisi

reviews.title: Works well can\'t enter decimal for photo deposit.
reviews.comment: Using a Galaxy S4 everything works fine except for the photo deposit.   I can\'t enter in a decimal amount to deposit my check.   My employer doesn\'t offer direct deposit so I was really looking forward to this feature.

reviews.title: Will not open
reviews.comment: This app worked for a few months but now it will no longer open. An error keeps occuring and then it says call a support service and provides no number... This was a very handy app and now it is useless. Fix it.

reviews.title: Updates crash the app
